Utterance.UttText: Ken harris, bed three, 71 yrs old under Dr Gregor, came in with arrhythmia.
He complained of chest pain this am and ECG was done and was reviewed by the team.
He was given some anginine and morphine for the pain.
Still tachycardic and new meds have been ordered in the medchart. still for pulse checks for one full minute.
His BP is just normal though he is scoring MEWS of 3 for the tachycardia.
